title.narrative: Support for national and district command and control

description.narrative: This activity (Support for national and district command and control) is a component of UK response to Ebola Crisis through support for the Joint Inter Agency Task Force (JIATF) reported by FCDO, with a funding type of 'Humanitarian assistance' and a budget of £7,303,395. This component benefits Sierra Leone, and works in the following sector(s): Relief co-ordination and support services. , with the following implementing partners: British High Commission, Crown Agents Limited, UK - Ministry of Defence. The start date is 29-10-2014 and the end date is 31-03-2016.
